OL,3,CWhy Starmer will struggle to survive
OL,4,Cthe Gorton humiliation
OL,6,FIt is not unusual for governing
OL,7,Fparties to be humiliated in by-
OL,8,Felections and to subsequently recover.
OL,9,FBut the trouncing of Labour in Gorton
OL,10,Fand Denton is something special. And
OL,11,Fit is especially damaging to the
OL,12,Fcareer prospects of the prime
OL,13,Fminister, Sir Keir Starmer.
OL,15,FThe electoral facts are astonishing,
OL,16,FDespite all the talk of it being a
OL,17,Fclose three way race, the Greens won
OL,18,Fwith a comfortable margin of 4,402 and
OL,19,Fsecured 41% of the vote, compared with
OL,20,FReform on 29% and Labour on 26%.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1772190104
OL,3,CWhy Starmer will struggle to survive
OL,4,Cthe Gorton humiliation
OL,6,FRemember that Labour secured 50.8% of
OL,7,Fthe vote in the 2024 general election
OL,8,Fand had a margin over its rivals of
OL,9,F36.7%, on a voter turnout almost
OL,10,Fidentical to yesterday's. Gorton and
OL,11,FDenton was, on that arithmetic, one of
OL,12,Fthe 10% of the seats that it took that
OL,13,Fshould have been easiest to retain.
OL,15,FOr to put it in the jargon, it has
OL,16,Flost one of its safest seats. And
OL,17,Fhaving lost Gorton, Labour could lose
OL,18,Falmost anywhere.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
