OL,3,CWhy Starmer will struggle to survive
OL,4,Cthe Gorton humiliation
OL,6,FFinally, the victory of the Greens is
OL,7,Fdevastating to Starmer's positioning
OL,8,Fof the party, under the powerful
OL,9,Finfluence of his former chief of
OL,10,Fstaff, Morgan McSweeney. He allowed
OL,11,Fthe Greens to flourish and grow, in
OL,12,Ffact, he encouraged it by positioning
OL,13,FLabour to the right, on everything
OL,14,Ffrom immigration to the EU to the
OL,15,Feconomy, because he and McSweeney saw
OL,16,Fthe main challenge as from Farage and
OL,17,FReform.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
