OL,3,CWhy Starmer will struggle to survive
OL,4,Cthe Gorton humiliation
OL,6,FFrom election night onward, this
OL,7,Falways seemed eccentric at best, since
OL,8,Fone of the conspicuous trends in that
OL,9,Felection was how well parties of the
OL,10,Fleft performed. If Starmer wanted to
OL,11,Fbe in power for the ten years he said
OL,12,Fwas necessary to change the country,
OL,13,Fhe always needed to position Labour as
OL,14,Fpart of a loose informal grouping that
OL,15,Fwould include the Lib Dems and the
OL,16,FGreens.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30308
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1772190104
OL,3,CWhy Starmer will struggle to survive
OL,4,Cthe Gorton humiliation
OL,6,FInstead, he set those parties up in
OL,7,Fmany voters' minds as the principled
OL,8,Falternatives to both Reform and
OL,9,FLabour. He could have taken the oxygen
OL,10,Faway from the Greens and the Lib Dems.
OL,11,FInstead, he fed them.
OL,13,FStarmer's Labour will also have been
OL,14,Fhurt in Gorton and Denton, with its
OL,15,Fsignificant Muslim and student
OL,16,Fcommunities, by his cautious approach
OL,17,Fto criticising the Israeli
OL,18,Fgovernment's strikes on Gaza and by
OL,19,Ftaking his pragmatic, friendly
OL,20,Fapproach to Trump.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
